UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. title.narrative: of targeted districts that produce reliable gender disaggregated data on the vulnerable and marginalized through DPMAS and use data for both subnational annual budget planning and national poverty monitoring

target.value: 2017:At least 15 priority districts produce and use gender disaggregated data

actual.value: 2017:With implementation of federal set up MOLFALD has commissioned an assessment to come up with suggested modifications and align with SDG indicators and 14th periodic plan goals.

title.narrative: Government administration of social protection benefits adopts unified MIS registration system and delivery innovations including electronic payment

target.value: 2017:Electronic payments reach 75% of child grant recipients by 2017

actual.value: 2017:MIS System Functional in 607 local governments and Electronic payment started in 100 local government.

title.narrative: Comprehensive multi-sector plan following National Social Protection Framework in place and Social Protection Act enacted

target.value: 2017:Framework in place by 2014 and Act enacted by 2016

actual.value: 2017:The Draft Social Protection Framework has been updated in line with federal context. It is with the National Planning Commission for finalisation.

title.narrative: of government-led evaluations in accordance with human-rights-based principles and OECD Development Assistance Committee (DAC) criteria in areas related to children and women, that contributed to a public debate and informed national policy documents and action plans

actual.value: 2017:Completed two evaluations on the UNICEF Project for the Reintegration and Rehabilitation of Children Affected by Armed Conflict in Nepal and National Plan of Action for Children in 2016. Evaluation of ECD led by NPC is underway and expected to be completed by early 2018.

title.narrative: Sectoral Plans and local government plans incorporate CFLG results/ indicators based on CFLG national strategy, integrating gender and equity perspective

actual.value: 2017:The result has been achieved in previous reporting year. (15 priority districts have completed the formulation of District Periodic Plans incorporating CFLG indicators, gender and social inclusion).

title.narrative: Child poverty priorities reflected in 3/5 Year Plan and Post 2015 comprehensive NPA for children

target.value: 2017:Child poverty investment priorities in 3/5 Year Plan and new NPA for children

actual.value: 2017:Child poverty work initiated in 2017 and should be reflected in next periodic plan.
